Corning Stockpiles $2 Billion of Metal, Wall Street Journal Says

-- B y   C l a u d i a   C a r p e n t e r
-- 
2011-02-16T06:18:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/corning-stockpiles-2-billion-of-metal-wall-street-journal-says.html
  Corning Inc . stockpiled $2 billion
of metal, mostly platinum and rhodium, for “certainty of the
price,” the Wall Street Journal reported, citing company
Treasurer Mark Rogus.   Approximately 20 percent of all consumer products, including
cars, electronics and pharmaceuticals, contain platinum or
require it for processing, according to the Journal, citing Jon
Nadler, an analyst at Kitco Metals Inc.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
